All four things (log + screenshot + Allure + email) can fire from one place — the pytest_runtest_makereport hook in conftest.py.
That hook runs after every test, no matter which assertion style you used (assert, expect(), or a validation helper).
So you write clean tests with plain assert and the hook captures everything centrally.
pytest calls this hook for every test, automatically.
rep.when == "call" = the test body ran (not setup/teardown).
rep.failed = it failed — however it failed.
